fields.data:
[global]
Linux_CIFS_method = gvfs
Linux_mountcifs_filemode = 0770
Linux_mountcifs_dirmode = 0770
Linux_mountcifs_options = rw,nobrl,noserverino,iocharset=utf8,sec=ntlm
Linux_gvfs_symlink = no
require_network = EPFL-Intranet
realm = EPFL-AD

[realm]
name = EPFL-AD
domain = {auth_domain}
username = {username}

[network]
name = Internet
ping = www.epfl.ch
ping = enacit.epfl.ch
ping = enclair.epfl.ch
error_msg = Error, you are not connected to the network. You won't be able to connect to this resource.

[network]
name = EPFL-Intranet
parent = Internet
cifs = files0.epfl.ch
cifs = files1.epfl.ch
cifs = files8.epfl.ch
cifs = files9.epfl.ch
cifs = enac1files.epfl.ch
error_msg = Error, you are not connected to the intranet of EPFL. Run a VPN client to be able to connect to this resource.
fields.name: Global

fields.data:
[msg] name = bug BADLOCK samba text = 2016-04-25 :
Due to recent security update on clients machines, default method to connect to NAS from Linux doesn't work yet any more.
We have submitted the issue to the concerned maintainers and expect a fix in the next few days.
In the mean time, you can switch ENACdrives default mount method to mount.cifs by following the documentation here, chapter 4.4.4.
You can contact Samuel Bancal for further information. ENAC-IT icon = critical
fields.name: test

[msg] name = bug BADLOCK samba text = 2016-04-25 :
Due to recent security update on clients machines, default method to connect to NAS from Linux doesn't work yet any more.
We have submitted the issue to the concerned maintainers and expect a fix in the next few days.
In the mean time, you can switch ENACdrives default mount method to mount.cifs by following the documentation here, chapter 4.4.4.
You can contact Samuel Bancal for further information. ENAC-IT icon = critical
